Welcome to Creamer Media’s Resources Watch, a weekly video round-up of the events and people making and shaping the news in the mining industry. This week: SAEC name change to Seriti Power signals coal miner’s new broader energy vision Hire jobless geologists to capture much-needed exploration data And, Menar expects first ore from inaugural manganese mine in July  The change of name of South African Energy Coal to Seriti Power when South32’s coal assets become absorbed into Seriti Resources from June is indicative of Sereti Resources seeing opportunities in general energy beyond coal. Seriti CEO Mike Teke:  A strong call for unemployed geology graduates to be contracted to capture historic exploration data electronically has been made by Letaba Elihle Investments.  LEI Principal Geology Consultant Siphelele Ntshangase:  Mining investment firm Menar has officially launched its first-to-portfolio manganese mine, East Manganese, in Hotazel, in the Northern Cape.  Menar MD Vuslat Bayoğlu:  For mining news as it breaks, stay logged onto Mining Weekly.com and register for our free daily newsletter.